<HR size="1" color="#5d7790">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
*note* DrowDaoc's Irc chat is at:<P> Irc.enterthegame.com Channel #drowdaoc<P>All members are encouraged to hang out there when possible.<P>1.) The current minimum requirement for DROWDAOC is level 40. Or a minimum of 700 skill in any one skill.<P>2.) One guilded alt once you have a level 45+ main.<P>2.) Punk teenagers, people who are offended by a little cursing, not always having a group, incapable of playing up to DROW standards, have limited playtime ability, NEED NOT BOTHER.<P>3.) Whining, bitching, moaning, in our guildchat is not permitted. Swearing is permitted, just don't act like a terrets patient. Any problems you have please post it in RANTS.<P>4.) Officers will be chosen by myself, do not ask me to be one. <P>5.) If you guild remove yourself you probably wont be let back in EVER. Guild hopping is not tolerated. I don't care what guild you came from. If you didn't like two or three different guilds you should probably go buy a solo rpg.<P>6.) Attacking another member either verbally or in any other room except rants is immediate suspension and most likely will get you removed immediately. Using racial slurs, epithets, gender based attacks, will also follow the same recourse.<P>7.) Grouping. Group with whom you choose. Unless it is a DROW sponsored event. I do however RECCOMMEND grouping guildmates over others when it is possible. EXCESSIVE use of non-drow members when DROW members are available to get in groups or shunning certain members will get you removed immediately and I wont give an explanation.<P>8.) I decide what guilds we ally with and what raids WE ALL go on. Feel free to go out and rvr as you wish or help out with other guilds on their raids on a perperson basis. IF I call a guild wide event however, it is a MUST that you attend, and proceed where directed immediately.<P>9.) I do RECCOMEND treating others on our server with repect, handing out rezzes when possible and NOT charging ever under any circumstances, helping out others on the server who have a question or might need some help. We aren't the boy-scouts but this isn't EQ everyone our server is part of the team.<P>10.) Fun is a necessity in DrowDaoc but the game will not always BE FUN in certain circumstances, if you cannot handle this, or any of the above rules feel free to let me know. I will take care of it.<P>11.) Reading of the forums and actively posting is recommended.<P>12.) INACTIVITY - If you are inactive for 30 days time you will be deleted from roster.<P>*All of these rules are subject to change, and to be interpreted by your GM and officers, at their discretion.<p>[ February 06, 2002: Message edited by: Hawken ]<P>--------------------<P>Hawken    <BR> <A HREF="mailto:Hawken@drow.org">Hawken@drow.org</A> <BR><B>GM</B> Drow Daoc   <BR><B>CORE Member</B>, Organization DROW<BR><I>Sponsors of Champion Internet Gaming Teams</I> <A HREF="http://www.drow.org/" TARGET=_blank>http://www.drow.org/</A> <BR> <IMG SRC="http://www.drow.org/images/spid.gif"> 
</FONT>
